HR Administrator – UAE National
Adecco
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 1 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Key tasks of the role will include; drafting contracts, liaising with the line and drafting the job briefs, managing, the group and life insurance policies, hard and soft copy filing and all on boarding and the induction processes for new starters in conjunction with the PRO.
Additionally, the role will also look after all of the travel requirements for staff within the office and be responsible for the day to day upkeep and maintenance of the office.
REQUIREMENTS
Requirements:
•Two to three years’ experience in an HR Administrator or similar role
•Bachelor degree in HR or related fields
•Excellent English Skills
•Assist the talent acquisition team to ensure manpower needs are being met
•Excellent knowledge of Microsoft office, Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Scheduling
ABOUT THE COMPANY
The Adecco Group is the world's leading provider of HR solutions. With more than 33,000 FTE employees and a network of 5,600 branches, in over 60 countries and territories around the world, we offer a wide variety of services, connecting close to 750,000 associates with well over 100,000 clients every day.
The services we offer fall into the broad categories of temporary staffing, permanent placement, career transition, talent development and workforce management solutions, as well as outsourcing and consulting.
The Adecco Group is based in Zurich-Glattbrugg, Switzerland and we are a Fortune Global 500 company listed on the SIX Swiss Exchange.
